						               													<description>Grindhouse! is a beautifully weird card game for two to four players set in the world of seventies B-movies. By collecting and playing production cards with the requisite values for the genre you're aiming for&amp;mdash;and whatever review you're aiming to get&amp;mdash;you complete a production and rake in bucks at the box office. Earn more money than your competition and you win the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players collect and play Production Cards onto productions, in separate horizontal rows on the table in front of them, and can work on up to two at a time. There are four different &amp;quot;roles&amp;quot; for Production Cards: Directors (yellow), Actors (blue), On Set (red), and Post (green). Each card has a numeric cost indicating how many cards you must discard to play it on a production and most have one or more value symbols: afros, blood, boobs, buildings, explosions, fists, wheels, and reels.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A production that contains all four roles can be wrapped (completed) by playing a Genre Card and Review Card onto it. Both cards show a value cost&amp;mdash;met or exceeded with the value symbols on the Production Cards&amp;mdash;and a box office haul for your completed film.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once a player has wrapped two productions (three in a two-player game), the game ends and box office receipts are totaled and the highest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
